# RES вҖ” Repair Execution System
## Mechanical Workshop Management System: Final System Architecture (v3 вҖ” Approved)

> [!NOTE]
> This is the **approved** architecture document. All feedback has been incorporated.
> Development starts with **Phase 1 (MVP)**.

---

## 1. Technology Stack

| Layer | Technology | Rationale |
|---|---|---|
| Language | Python 3.11+ | Your stack |
| UI Framework | **PySide6** | Qt for desktop MES-style dashboards, dark theme, kiosk mode |
| i18n / Translations | **Qt Linguist** (`QTranslator` + `.ts`/`.qm` files) | English + Spanish from day one; new languages = new `.ts` file |
| Database (Dev) | **SQLite** | Zero-config, instant setup |
| Database (Prod) | **PostgreSQL** | Multi-user, LAN/cloud access; same SQLAlchemy code |
| ORM | **SQLAlchemy** | Switch DB with one config line; never raw SQL |
| WhatsApp/SMS (MVP) | `pywhatkit` | Local testing only |
| WhatsApp/SMS (Prod) | **Twilio API** | Reliable, programmatic вҖ” **for clients only** |
| Charts/KPIs | **PyQtGraph** | Fast real-time charts embedded in Qt, low resource use |
| Config/Secrets | `.env` + `python-dotenv` | Never hardcode keys |
| Security | `bcrypt` + SQLAlchemy parameterized queries + TLS | See Section 9 |
| Packaging | **PyInstaller** | Distribute as `.exe` on workshop PCs |
| AI Cost Estimator | OpenAI Vision API вҶ’ local YOLOv8 | Subproject; requirements TBD |

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **WhatsApp and SMS notifications are for clients only.** Insurance companies access the system through their own dedicated **Insurance Dashboard** (a role-restricted view within the same application), not through messaging.

