## 3. Repair Process Pipeline

### Routing by Crash Severity

```
Vehicle Reception
      в”Ӯ
      в–ј
  Crash Severity?
  в”ңв”Җ HIGH в”Җв”Җв–ә Mechanic в”Җв”Җв–ә Straightening в”Җв”Җв–ә Preparation to Paint
  в””в”Җ LOW  в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв–ә Straightening в”Җв”Җв–ә Preparation to Paint
                                                    в”Ӯ
                                                    в–ј
                                                Painting
                                                    в”Ӯ
                                                    в–ј
                                                Assembly
                                                    в”Ӯ
                                                    в–ј
                                               Polishing
                                                    в”Ӯ
                                                    в–ј
                                           Quality Assurance
                                           в”ңв”Җ PASS в”Җв”Җв–ә Delivery
                                           в””в”Җ FAIL в”Җв”Җв–ә ROLLBACK to ANY prior process
                                                       (with reason + manager approval)
```

> [!NOTE]
> QA fail вҖ” and any other rollback вҖ” can target **any** prior process in the pipeline, not just the immediately previous one. The mechanic selects the target process and provides a written reason.

### Process Table (DB-Seeded вҖ” Add new processes without code changes)

| Seq | Process Name | Condition |
|---|---|---|
| 1 | Vehicle Reception | Always |
| 2 | Mechanic Work | High severity only |
| 3 | Straightening | Always |
| 4 | Preparation to Paint | Always |
| 5 | Painting | Always |
| 6 | Assembly | Always |
| 7 | Polishing | Always |
| 8 | Quality Assurance | Always |

---

## 4. Database Schema

### Tables Overview

| Table | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `customers` | Client data |
| `insurance_companies` | Insurer data |
| `vehicles` | Core entity; linked to customer + insurer |
| `processes` | Pipeline config (sequence, capacity, hours) |
| `process_logs` | Check-in/out timestamps per vehicle per process |
| `process_transitions` | Transit time between checkout of process A and checkin to B |
| `process_rollbacks` | Vehicle returns to prior step: who, why, when, target process |
| `findings` | Damage found during repair; cost, SLA timestamps |
| `parts` | Parts inventory |
| `suppliers` | Parts suppliers |
| `repair_parts_used` | Parts consumed per vehicle |
| `users` | Staff with roles (mechanic / manager / admin / insurance-viewer) |
| `notification_log` | Audit trail of every client WhatsApp/SMS sent |

### Key Fields

**`processes`** includes:
- `max_capacity` вҖ” how many vehicles the bay can hold simultaneously
- `sequence_order` вҖ” determines pipeline order
- `required_severity` вҖ” NULL = always; 'HIGH' = mechanic only

**`process_logs`** includes:
- `checkin_time`, `checkout_time` вҖ” primary KPI source for all stakeholders
- `actual_hours` vs. `estimated_hours` вҖ” variance = cost variance
- `status` вҖ” waiting / in_progress / completed / rolled_back

**`process_transitions`** includes:
- `transit_minutes` вҖ” time between checkout A and checkin B
- Captures whether delay is due to capacity (bay full) or staff (bay available but vehicle not moved)

**`findings`** includes:
- `reported_at` вҖ” when finding was recorded
- `insurance_acknowledged_at` вҖ” when insurer confirmed receipt (SLA KPI)
- `approved_at` вҖ” when budget was approved
- `cost_estimator_ref` вҖ” **nullable hook** for future AI cost estimator integration

**`process_rollbacks`** includes:
- `from_process_id`, `to_process_id` вҖ” can jump multiple steps back
- `reason` вҖ” mandatory text
- `approved_by`, `approved_at` вҖ” full audit trail

### Capacity Tracking

Each process has `max_capacity` (configurable). The system:
1. Shows **current occupancy vs. capacity** on the dashboard for each bay
2. When a vehicle checks out, the system checks if the next process has available space
3. If capacity is full вҶ’ status shown as **"Waiting вҖ” Bay Full"** (capacity block)
4. If capacity is free but vehicle is not moved вҶ’ timer flags as **"Waiting вҖ” Staff Delay"**
5. Both waiting reasons are logged in `process_logs.status` for reporting

---

## 5. Key Workflows

### 5.1 Check-in to a Process
```
Operator: Select vehicle вҶ’ Select process вҶ’ Click "Check In"
вҶ’ Creates PROCESS_LOG with checkin_time = now()
вҶ’ Sends client WhatsApp/SMS: "Vehicle has entered [Process Name]"
вҶ’ Dashboard refreshes: vehicle shows in that process bay with live timer
вҶ’ Bay occupancy counter increments
```

### 5.2 Check-out from a Process
```
Operator: Click "Check Out"
вҶ’ PROCESS_LOG: checkout_time = now(), actual_hours calculated
вҶ’ PROCESS_TRANSITION recorded: transit_minutes begins counting  
вҶ’ Client WhatsApp/SMS: "Vehicle completed [Process Name]"
вҶ’ Dashboard: vehicle moves to "In Transit" state
вҶ’ Bay occupancy counter decrements
```

### 5.3 Finding Discovered
```
Mechanic: "Report Finding"
вҶ’ findings_dialog: description, cost (manual for now), optional photo
   [Future hook: "Use Cost Estimator" button вҶ’ will call AI engine]
вҶ’ FINDING created with reported_at = now()
вҶ’ Insurance Dashboard: immediately shows new finding alert (red badge)
вҶ’ Insurer views finding in their dashboard вҶ’ clicks "Acknowledge"
   вҶ’ insurance_acknowledged_at stamped (SLA measured)
вҶ’ Insurer approves budget вҶ’ approved_at stamped
вҶ’ Repair continues
```

### 5.4 Process Rollback / QA Fail
```
Manager/QA: "Roll Back Vehicle"
вҶ’ rollback_dialog:
   - Select TARGET process (any prior, not just previous)
   - Write mandatory reason
вҶ’ Requires manager/admin role approval
вҶ’ PROCESS_ROLLBACK record created (from, to, reason, approved_by, approved_at)
вҶ’ New PROCESS_LOG checkin created at target process
вҶ’ Vehicle timeline shows rollback event clearly in history
вҶ’ Nothing is ever deleted вҖ” full audit trail
```

---

## 6. Stakeholder Views

### 6.1 Workshop Dashboard (Manager/Admin)
- Kanban board: one column per process, vehicle cards with elapsed timer
- Bay capacity indicators: e.g. "Painting: 2/3 bays used"
- Waiting vehicles: color-coded (capacity block vs. staff delay)
- Alerts panel: findings awaiting insurer acknowledgment
- Real-time auto-refresh every 30 seconds (`QTimer`)

### 6.2 Insurance Company Dashboard *(in-system, role-restricted)*
- Accessible via login with role `insurance-viewer`
- Each insurer sees **only their own vehicles**
- KPIs: check-in/out timestamps, actual vs. estimated time, time saved, cost reduction
- Findings queue: pending acknowledgment + budget approval
- SLA metrics: average time from finding вҶ’ acknowledgment вҶ’ approval
- No WhatsApp/SMS вҖ” the dashboard is their communication channel

### 6.3 Client Notifications (WhatsApp/SMS only)
- Check-in / check-out вҶ’ automated message per process
- Finding discovered вҶ’ "Additional work found, awaiting insurance approval"
- QA Pass вҶ’ "Your vehicle is ready for pickup"
- All logged in `notification_log`

### 6.4 Workshop Floor Kiosk View
- Fullscreen PySide6 on any networked PC
- Shows all active vehicles, current process bay, elapsed time
- Color-coded: on-time (green), near deadline (amber), overdue (red)
- No PII displayed (license plate only, no names)

