## 7. Internationalization (i18n)

English and Spanish supported from day one. New languages can be added later without code changes.

| Tool | Role |
|---|---|
| `QTranslator` (Qt built-in) | Loads `.qm` translation file at runtime |
| `Qt Linguist` | Manages `.ts` source translation files |
| `lupdate` | Extracts all translatable strings from Python source |
| `lrelease` | Compiles `.ts` вҶ’ `.qm` binary used by Qt |

**Implementation rule**: Every user-facing string in Python must use `self.tr("...")` or `QCoreApplication.translate(...)`. Never hardcode display text. This is enforced from the first line of UI code.

```
assets/
в””в”Җв”Җ translations/
    в”ңв”Җв”Җ res_en.ts   вҶҗ English source
    в”ңв”Җв”Җ res_es.ts   вҶҗ Spanish source
    в”ңв”Җв”Җ res_en.qm   вҶҗ Compiled English binary
    в””в”Җв”Җ res_es.qm   вҶҗ Compiled Spanish binary
```

Language switch is available in Settings вҖ” no restart required.

